        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 1:21AM PDT by NWS Elko NV</headline>
        <description>At 120 AM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Monitor Valley, or 21 miles northeast of Round Mountain, moving
northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust reducing
visibilities.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Monitor Valley around 130 AM PDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
